de.ityx.ocr.ocrservice.vocr.features

Class CorpusCharacterDictionary

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.ityx.ocr.ocrservice.vocr.features.CorpusCharacterDictionary
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class CorpusCharacterDictionary
extends Object
implements Serializable
    A dictionary that maps character labels to integer values that can be used to encode and decode the labels for the Classifier. Only single graphemes are explicitly recorded. Strings with more than a single grapheme are mapped to UNDEFINED_CONTENT and UNDEFINED_INDEX, respectively.

      • prepare

        public void prepare()
        Prunes the dictionary with respect to the given parameter values in CorpusCharacterDictionary(int, int).
        • All labels that are less often observed than the given minCount parameter are pruned.
        • Labels are ranked by their frequency. Only the top-k most frequent labels are explicitly incorporated in the dictionary. (k=maxElements)
        • Labels that are pruned are mapped to UNDEFINED_INDEX.
